Gymshark Train
We train. We motivate. We grow. Together.
Step up your game and join the family, so we can #GymsharkTrain together 🦈

Get ready to sweat with @scottw_jordan 💦 This epic full body workout can be done right from your living room floor. All you need is a set of dumbbells 💪 Let’s go Gymshark fam 🦈

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Get ready to make that full body work with this powerful at-home HIIT workout from @mrandmrsmuscle 💪 
Tag a friend who you would duo this with!
#Gymsharktrain

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

@wozldn brings you a 🔥 full body workout to celebrate the last day of #Gymshark66! Expect 30 minutes of dynamic and energetic H.I.I.T exercises – you're defo going to need some water 🥵

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

node.text:
This one is gonna take your ab burn to the next level 🔥
Tag a gym bro to try this with 👇
📸: @georgebamfojr
#GymsharkTrain

Really fire up those back muscles with this complete pull workout from @whitneyysimmons 🔥
1️⃣ Conventional deadlifts (10,8,6,4)
2️⃣ Landmine close grip row (3x8)
3️⃣ Rotating hammer to wide bicep curl (3x10)
4️⃣ Cable stretchers (3x10)
5️⃣ Superset: Cable hammer curl + High to low face pulls (3x10)
#GymsharkTrain

node.accessibility_caption:
Brittany Lupton performs a glute and hamstring focused leg workout while wearing the Gymshark Adapt Camo Leggings in black and Training Bandeau in burgundy. 

The first exercise is 3 sets of 10 deadlifts, followed by 2 reps at a max weight. The next exercise Brittany performs is barbell hip thrusts for 4 sets of 8-10 reps. Exercise three is 10 single leg deadlifts for 4 sets. Brittany uses the Smith machine to do this, bending one leg at the knee and pushing it backwards as she lowers the bar down. The final exercise is 10 back extensions where she holds a weight plate to her chest while lowering her upper body down to just below horizontal and back up again. She does this for 4 sets.

node.text:
Grow those glutes & hamstrings with this tight routine 🍑
Save + follow along with @_brittanylupton:
✔️ Deadlifts (3x10 + 1x2)
✔️ Hip thrusts (4x8-10)
✔️ Single leg deadlifts (4x10)
✔️ Back extensions (4x10)
#GymsharkTrain #GymsharkWomen

node.text:
Tuesday Choose-Day full body challenge 👭
Pick a partner and challenge them to join you in this @adotty10 + @littletfitness circuit by leaving an @ for them in the comments 🏆
1️⃣ 180 burpee jumps
2️⃣ Pushup clap + Dip
3️⃣ Alt. Bulgarian split squat
4️⃣ Reverse leg lifts
5️⃣ Bunny hops
45 secs on | 15 secs off | 4x rounds
#GymsharkTrain

node.accessibility_caption:
@sophjbutler performs a dumbbells only chest workout while wearing the Gymshark Adapt Animal Sports Bra and matching Leggings in teal. 

The first exercise is an incline dumbbell chest press. Sophie does the first set of 15 reps as a warm up, and then does 3 sets with 10-12 reps. Here, she leans slightly back so her body is slanted, starting with her arms bent at shoulder height and pushing upwards until fully extended over her head. The second exercise is incline dumbbell flyes for 3 sets of 10-12 reps. Again, leaning back at a slight angle in her wheelchair, Sophie starts with her arms straight out in front of her chest and then extends them outward to either side of her body, keeping them at shoulder height. Exercise three is a superset with upright dumbbell flyes followed by dumbbell punches. She does this for 3 sets of 10-12 reps. For the flyes, Sophie starts with her arms by her side and then brings one arm at a time up and across her body until at face height, with her wrist facing upwards. For the punches, she punches across her body, making sure to really extend her arm and keep her core tight. The final exercise is 12-15 incline pinch press, done for 3 sets. For this exercise, Sophie's fingers are interlocked around the dumbbell ensuring her arms maintain a narrow position. She then brings the dumbbell down towards her chest, keeping her elbows tucked in at her side as she does so.

node.accessibility_caption:
@elliotbfit performs 3 simple bicep exercises while wearing the Gymshark Critical Zip Joggers in light green and Critical Sleeveless Tee in black. 

The first exercise is 4 sets of 10 seated bicep curls using dumbbells. Exercise two is 4 sets of seated hammer curls, also for 10 reps. The final exercise is straight bar curls for 4 sets of 8-10 reps. Here, Elliot makes sure to extend fully downwards towards the top of his thighs, and then bring the bar back up to around shoulder height.

node.text:
3 quick, simple + effective bicep exercises. No need to over complicate things ✔️
1️⃣ Seated bicep curls (4x10)
2️⃣ Seated hammer curls (4x10)
3️⃣ Straight bar curls (4x8-10)
📸: @elliotbfit
#GymsharkTrain

This #MotivationalReel will set your weekend training mood 🙌
📸: @gainsbybrains
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
It's a double leg day today because why not... 🏋️‍♂️
1️⃣ Hack squat (4x12)
2️⃣ Bulgarian squat (4x8)
3️⃣ Leg extension (4x12)
4️⃣ Hip thrust (4x12)
Tag a leg day lover who must try this routine ⬇️
📸: @grosgui_fit 
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
Make your comeback to the gym with this ultimate leg day routine 🦵 🏋️‍♀️
1️⃣ 7-7-7 hip thrusts (3 sets)
2️⃣ DB double contraction sumo squat (3x10)
Superset with...
3️⃣ Double contraction RDL (3x10)
4️⃣ Box jump combo (3x8)
📸: @libbychristensen 
#GymsharkTrain

Here's the leg day routine you won't wanna miss this week 🔥
1️⃣ Squat (3x12)
2️⃣ Leg curl (3x8)
3️⃣ Single arm kettlebell front squat (3x8 each leg)
4️⃣ Dumbbell box step up (3x8)
5️⃣ Burpee to box jump (4x5)
We're here to see you make those moves and keep you pushing forwards. Tag us in your workout videos with #GymsharkTrain
📸: @m3colby
